## 0.9.1 Minor Release

Focus: Stability, robustness, reliability, security hardening, and test coverage. Finish polishing existing features instead of adding new ones.

### ✅ Goals:

* Fix high-priority bugs in existing features
* Improve robustness and reliability of core flows
* Harden authentication, file handling, update flow, and plugin safety
* Expand automated test coverage for auth, file, share, and invalid-input cases
* Improve logging, error handling, and restart/update safety
* Polish existing admin and maintenance capabilities

#### 🛡️ Reliability / Security / Testing First

* [ ] Triage and fix the high-priority bugs listed in the code review summary
* [ ] Prioritize hardening over new features for 0.9.1
* [ ] Treat new features as 0.10.0 work unless they directly support robustness/testing
* [ ] Define a minimal 0.9.1 release gate: key bugs fixed, core tests passing, no known critical security issue

#### 🔍 Search Parser

* [x] Design search expression grammar (support `&`, `|`, `NOT`, `TAG`, `TYPE`)
* [x] Implement parser (possibly with `lark`, `pyparsing`, or hand-rolled recursive descent)
* [x] Integrate with file metadata and filtering logic
* [ ] Add test cases for parsing edge cases
* [ ] Add fallback mode: `"abc"` as fuzzy substring match

#### 📁 File Sorting

* [x] Add UI control (e.g., dropdown: Name, Size, Time)
* [x] Backend sorting logic
* [x] Store last used sort option in session

#### 🌐 Torrent Support (Deferred)

* [ ] Defer torrent support to 0.10.0 unless it is needed for testing/refactoring existing download infrastructure
* [ ] Choose backend library (e.g. `libtorrent`, `aria2`, `webtorrent`)
* [ ] Provide basic UI for adding `.torrent` file or magnet link
* [ ] Monitor progress and display file list
* [ ] Route downloaded content into user’s cloud directory

#### 🪵 Logging

* [ ] Add structured log statements to major code paths (e.g., file ops, auth, system ops)
* [ ] Support toggling debug/info level in config
* [ ] Route logs to rotating log file or journald
* [ ] Query and configure logs on web UI by administrator
* [ ] Add secure cookie settings (`SameSite`, configurable `secure`, cookie clear on logout)
* [ ] Harden auth API input validation and error handling (missing JSON fields, invalid request body, consistent status codes)
* [ ] Remove global database connection import from routes; use `current_app.conn` or app context instead

#### 🙅 Custom 404 page

* [ ] Custom 404 page in the style of *-theme.css 

#### ⚙️ Auto-restart for non-docker installation

* [ ] Auto-restart for non-docker installation

#### 📊 Export and import database

* [ ] Admin user can export and import database from web.

#### 🔐 Security Hardening

* [ ] Replace weak password hash salt scheme in `db/auth.py` (`gen_salt('md5')`) with a stronger password hash
* [ ] Define explicit read/write/delete permissions for shared-link paths
* [ ] Normalize and validate virtual paths / uploaded filenames before inserting into DB
* [ ] Review auth/session cookies: `SameSite`, configurable `secure`, and explicit cookie clearing on logout
* [ ] Add checksum/signature validation and structure checks for plugin zip installation
* [ ] Harden update/install flows that unzip remote archives into the application/plugin directories

#### 🧱 Robustness and Maintainability

* [ ] Remove global DB connection imports from routes; use `current_app.conn` / app context
* [ ] Add centralized permission/session guard helper or decorators for routes
* [ ] Add request-body validation for auth/file/system APIs (missing JSON, invalid types, bad content-type)
* [ ] Return more appropriate HTTP status codes (`400/401/403/...`) instead of always returning `200` with `FAIL`
* [ ] Add timeouts and exception handling for update/version-check network requests
* [ ] Replace broad `pkill python` / `pkill gunicorn` restart logic with safer process management
* [ ] Replace `os.system(...)` update/install shell calls with safer subprocess usage
* [ ] Use context-managed cursors / ensure cursor close in all DB helper paths
* [ ] Revisit `check_session()` cleanup strategy so every request does not first delete expired sessions globally
* [ ] Add locking / safer state management for HTTP download task progress

#### 🧪 Test Completion

* [ ] Move from a fixed local DB DSN to a clearer isolated test database / test config
* [ ] Improve test isolation (avoid one shared mutable DB state across the whole test session)
* [ ] Add API tests for invalid JSON bodies, missing fields, permission failures, and file/share edge cases
* [ ] Add tests for auth/session cookie behavior and logout cleanup
* [ ] Add regression tests for every high-priority bug fixed in 0.9.1
* [ ] Define a small 0.9.1 test matrix for auth, file CRUD, sharing, external link, and HTTP download tasks

---

## 0.10.0 Major Release

Focus: New features and larger refactors after 0.9.1 hardening is complete.

### ✅ Goals:

* Pick up deferred feature work after 0.9.1 hardening/test completion
* Full WebDAV support (start from scratch)
* Plugin website / plugin manager
* Basic unit and integration tests
* Code refactor for clarity and structure
* Add file version control
* Add media streaming support
* Disk management UI improvements
* Optional systemd-based deployment mode (non-Docker)
* Backup system (disk mount + config)
* Better UI on mobile devices

### 📝 TODO List:

#### 🌐 WebDAV Support

* [ ] Create a standalone WebDAV layer (either from spec or use `wsgidav`)
* [ ] Map routes to Squirrel's file provider
* [ ] Support PROPFIND, GET, PUT, DELETE
* [ ] Permissions integration
* [ ] WebDAV-specific tests

#### 🔌 Plugin Website

* [ ] Build plugin index frontend (listing + search)
* [ ] Design plugin metadata format (e.g., `plugin.json`)
* [ ] Add in-app plugin manager (install/enable/remove)

#### 🧪 Testing System

* [ ] Set up `pytest` framework
* [ ] Write tests for core features (auth, file CRUD, tag, search)
* [ ] Add disk mounting mock tests (non-root)
* [ ] Optionally run CI via GitHub Actions

#### ♻️ Code Refactor

* [ ] Split platform-dependent logic (Docker vs native)
* [ ] Abstract restart logic, system tools, env detection
* [ ] Move disk/system logic to `core/system/`
* [ ] Rename unclear variables/functions

#### 🕘 File Version Control

* [ ] Decide versioning method: file copies or content diffs
* [ ] Track metadata: versions, timestamps, deltas
* [ ] UI for viewing, comparing, and restoring past versions

#### 🎥 Media Streaming

* [ ] Add MIME detection and `Content-Range` support for video
* [ ] Support progressive streaming
* [ ] Optional transcoding backend (e.g., `ffmpeg`, `streamlink`)

#### 🎨 Better Disk Management UI

* [ ] Redesign disk panel (list, partitions, RAID, format options)
* [ ] Show mount status, usage, filesystem type
* [ ] UI triggers system calls or squirrel-agent

#### 💾 Backup System

* [ ] User config for backup mount (path, schedule, target disk)
* [ ] UI for creating backup configuration
* [ ] Scheduled task (or manual trigger) to sync data
* [ ] Detect disk availability

#### 🖥️ Systemd Native Deployment Support

* [ ] Provide install script for systemd deployment
* [ ] Create service unit template
* [ ] Document restart behavior without Docker

#### 👌 UI Improvements

* [ ] Use more icon instead of text and emoji
* [ ] Enhance UI for mobile devices

